	"description": [
		"This course equips students to act ethically in for-profit and non-profit business settings by introducing diverse ethical frameworks and encouraging the use of personal character strengths. Learners engage with moral dilemmas using these frameworks, complete a virtue profile analyzing their top five strengths, and participate in reflection posts and case studies to critically assess their ethical perspectives. Offered annually in the spring. Prerequisite: BUS 110 Fundamentals of Business or by permission of the instructor."
